109/* Find key string in table. */
110static key_code
111key_string_search_table(const char *string)
112{
113 u_int i, user;
114
115 for (i = 0; i < nitems(key_string_table); i++) {
116 if (strcasecmp(string, key_string_table[i].string) == 0)
117 return (key_string_table[i].key);
118 }
119
120 if (sscanf(string, "User%u", &user) == 1 && user < KEYC_NUSER)
121 return (KEYC_USER + user);
122
123 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
124}
125
126/* Find modifiers. */
127static key_code
128key_string_get_modifiers(const char **string)
129{
130 key_code modifiers;
131
132 modifiers = 0;
133 while (((*string)[0] != '\0') && (*string)[1] == '-') {
134 switch ((*string)[0]) {
135 case 'C':
136 case 'c':
137 modifiers |= KEYC_CTRL;
138 break;
139 case 'M':
140 case 'm':
141 modifiers |= KEYC_ESCAPE;
142 break;
143 case 'S':
144 case 's':
145 modifiers |= KEYC_SHIFT;
146 break;
147 default:
148 *string = NULL;
149 return (0);
150 }
151 *string += 2;
152 }
153 return (modifiers);
154}
155
156/* Lookup a string and convert to a key value. */
157key_code
158key_string_lookup_string(const char *string)
159{
160 static const char *other = "!#()+,-.0123456789:;<=>?'\r\t";
161 key_code key;
162 u_int u;
163 key_code modifiers;
164 struct utf8_data ud;
165 u_int i;
166 enum utf8_state more;
167 wchar_t wc;
168
169 /* Is this no key or any key? */
170 if (strcasecmp(string, "None") == 0)
171 return (KEYC_NONE);
172 if (strcasecmp(string, "Any") == 0)
173 return (KEYC_ANY);
174
175 /* Is this a hexadecimal value? */
176 if (string[0] == '0' && string[1] == 'x') {
177 if (sscanf(string + 2, "%x", &u) != 1)
178 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
179 if (u > 0x1fffff)
180 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
181 return (u);
182 }
183
184 /* Check for modifiers. */
185 modifiers = 0;
186 if (string[0] == '^' && string[1] != '\0') {
187 modifiers |= KEYC_CTRL;
188 string++;
189 }
190 modifiers |= key_string_get_modifiers(&string);
191 if (string == NULL || string[0] == '\0')
192 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
193
194 /* Is this a standard ASCII key? */
195 if (string[1] == '\0' && (u_char)string[0] <= 127) {
196 key = (u_char)string[0];
197 if (key < 32 || key == 127)
198 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
199 } else {
200 /* Try as a UTF-8 key. */
201 if ((more = utf8_open(&ud, (u_char)*string)) == UTF8_MORE) {
202 if (strlen(string) != ud.size)
203 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
204 for (i = 1; i < ud.size; i++)
205 more = utf8_append(&ud, (u_char)string[i]);
206 if (more != UTF8_DONE)
207 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
208 if (utf8_combine(&ud, &wc) != UTF8_DONE)
209 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
210 return (wc | modifiers);
211 }
212
213 /* Otherwise look the key up in the table. */
214 key = key_string_search_table(string);
215 if (key == KEYC_UNKNOWN)
216 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
217 }
218
219 /* Convert the standard control keys. */
220 if (key < KEYC_BASE && (modifiers & KEYC_CTRL) && !strchr(other, key)) {
221 if (key >= 97 && key <= 122)
222 key -= 96;
223 else if (key >= 64 && key <= 95)
224 key -= 64;
225 else if (key == 32)
226 key = 0;
227 else if (key == 63)
228 key = KEYC_BSPACE;
229 else
230 return (KEYC_UNKNOWN);
231 modifiers &= ~KEYC_CTRL;
232 }
233
234 return (key | modifiers);
235}
236
237/* Convert a key code into string format, with prefix if necessary. */
238const char *
239key_string_lookup_key(key_code key)
240{
241 static char out[32];
242 char tmp[8];
243 u_int i;
244 struct utf8_data ud;
245 size_t off;
246
247 *out = '\0';
248
249 /* Handle no key. */
250 if (key == KEYC_NONE)
251 return ("None");
252
253 /* Handle special keys. */
254 if (key == KEYC_UNKNOWN)
255 return ("Unknown");
256 if (key == KEYC_ANY)
257 return ("Any");
258 if (key == KEYC_FOCUS_IN)
259 return ("FocusIn");
260 if (key == KEYC_FOCUS_OUT)
261 return ("FocusOut");
262 if (key == KEYC_PASTE_START)
263 return ("PasteStart");
264 if (key == KEYC_PASTE_END)
265 return ("PasteEnd");
266 if (key == KEYC_MOUSE)
267 return ("Mouse");
268 if (key == KEYC_DRAGGING)
269 return ("Dragging");
270 if (key == KEYC_MOUSEMOVE_PANE)
271 return ("MouseMovePane");
272 if (key == KEYC_MOUSEMOVE_STATUS)
273 return ("MouseMoveStatus");
274 if (key == KEYC_MOUSEMOVE_BORDER)
275 return ("MouseMoveBorder");
276 if (key >= KEYC_USER && key < KEYC_USER + KEYC_NUSER) {
277 snprintf(out, sizeof out, "User%u", (u_int)(key - KEYC_USER));
278 return (out);
279 }
280
281 /*
282 * Special case: display C-@ as C-Space. Could do this below in
283 * the (key >= 0 && key <= 32), but this way we let it be found
284 * in key_string_table, for the unlikely chance that we might
285 * change its name.
286 */
287 if ((key & KEYC_MASK_KEY) == 0)
288 key = ' ' | KEYC_CTRL | (key & KEYC_MASK_MOD);
289
290 /* Fill in the modifiers. */
291 if (key & KEYC_CTRL)
292 strlcat(out, "C-", sizeof out);
293 if (key & KEYC_ESCAPE)
294 strlcat(out, "M-", sizeof out);
295 if (key & KEYC_SHIFT)
296 strlcat(out, "S-", sizeof out);
297 key &= KEYC_MASK_KEY;
298
299 /* Try the key against the string table. */
300 for (i = 0; i < nitems(key_string_table); i++) {
301 if (key == key_string_table[i].key)
302 break;
303 }
304 if (i != nitems(key_string_table)) {
305 strlcat(out, key_string_table[i].string, sizeof out);
306 return (out);
307 }
308
309 /* Is this a UTF-8 key? */
310 if (key > 127 && key < KEYC_BASE) {
311 if (utf8_split(key, &ud) == UTF8_DONE) {
312 off = strlen(out);
313 memcpy(out + off, ud.data, ud.size);
314 out[off + ud.size] = '\0';
315 return (out);
316 }
317 }
318
319 /* Invalid keys are errors. */
320 if (key == 127 || key > 255) {
321 snprintf(out, sizeof out, "Invalid#%llx", key);
322 return (out);
323 }
324
325 /* Check for standard or control key. */
326 if (key <= 32) {
327 if (key == 0 || key > 26)
328 xsnprintf(tmp, sizeof tmp, "C-%c", (int)(64 + key));
329 else
330 xsnprintf(tmp, sizeof tmp, "C-%c", (int)(96 + key));
331 } else if (key >= 32 && key <= 126) {
332 tmp[0] = key;
333 tmp[1] = '\0';
334 } else if (key >= 128)
335 xsnprintf(tmp, sizeof tmp, "\\%llo", key);
336
337 strlcat(out, tmp, sizeof out);
338 return (out);
339}
